    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-15T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="655"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/11916: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1941-11-15T17:00:00+03:00">November 15, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 16—8:21 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1929. The Soviet press reports that Litvinov has been appointed an Assistant
                    People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs and that Oumanski has been appointed a
                    member of the Collegium of the <pb facs="0670" n="658" xml:id="pg_658"/>
                    People’s Commissariat for Foreign Affairs. Oumanski has also been made director
                    of Tass.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
